# FinLLM

FinLLM is a from-scratch, finance-domain decoder-only Transformer language model.
It is built around the local financial corpus and SentencePiece tokenizer already in
this folder, with a production-style training pipeline: streaming tokenization,
binary memory-mapped datasets, typed configs, checkpointing, evaluation, and
sampling.

This is intentionally honest engineering: it is not pretending to be GPT-4 scale.
It is a serious miniature LLM system that shows the same core ideas used in larger
systems: corpus construction, subword tokenization, causal attention, stable
training loops, reproducible configs, validation loss, perplexity, and inference.

## Why this is strong for a CV

- Built a domain-specific language model from scratch in PyTorch.
- Implemented both a legacy GPT-style stack and a more modern compact LLM stack
  with RMSNorm, RoPE, grouped-query attention, SwiGLU, tied embeddings, top-k and
  top-p sampling, repetition penalties, AdamW parameter grouping, cosine
  learning-rate decay, gradient accumulation, gradient clipping, and checkpoint
  resume.
- Designed a scalable data pipeline that streams a large text corpus into compact
  `train.bin` and `val.bin` memory maps instead of loading all text into RAM.
- Trained with a custom 32k SentencePiece BPE tokenizer for financial filings and
  news text.
- Added model-card documentation, reproducible JSON configs, smoke tests, and CLI
  entrypoints for preparation, training, evaluation, and generation.

